SUMMARY:🍳 Breakfast: Overnight Oats
DESCRIPTION:Recipe: Overnight Oats\nServings: 2\nPrep: 5 min | Total: 5 min\n\n--- Ingredients ---\n• 1 cup rolled oats\n• 1 cup milk\n• 0.5 cup greek yogurt\n• 2 tbsp honey\n• 0.5 cup blueberries\n• 2 tbsp chia seeds\n\n--- Steps ---\n1. Combine oats, milk, yogurt, honey, and chia seeds in a jar or container.\n2. Stir well, cover, and refrigerate overnight (or at least 4 hours).\n3. Top with blueberries before serving. Eat cold or microwave 1-2 min.\n\nTip: Swap blueberries for banana, strawberries, or any fruit. Add peanut butter for extra protein.
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mealplan-20260418-lunch-17@mealplanner
DTSTAMP:20260419T112952Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260418T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260418T130000
SUMMARY:🥗 Lunch: Chicken Stir Fry
DESCRIPTION:Recipe: Chicken Stir Fry\nServings: 4\nPrep: 15 min | Cook: 10 min | Total: 25 min\n\n--- Ingredients ---\n• 1.5 lb chicken breast\n• 2 tbsp soy sauce\n• 1 tbsp sesame oil\n• 1 tbsp cornstarch\n• 2 cup broccoli florets\n• 1 red bell pepper\n• 2 clove garlic\n• 1 tbsp fresh ginger\n• 2 cup rice\n• 1 tbsp vegetable oil\n\n--- Steps ---\n1. Slice chicken breast into thin strips and toss with cornstarch, 1 tbsp soy sauce, and sesame oil.\n2. Cook rice according to package directions.\n3. Heat vegetable oil in a wok or large skillet over high heat.\n4. Add chicken and cook 4-5 minutes until golden. Remove and set aside.\n5. Add garlic, ginger, broccoli, and bell pepper. Stir fry 3-4 minutes.\n6. Return chicken to wok, add remaining soy sauce, toss to combine.\n7. Serve over rice.\n\nTip: Works great with any vegetables you have on hand. Snap peas and carrots are good swaps.
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
